From: Gaggery Tsai <gaggery.tsai@intel.com>
Date: Wed, 9 Apr 2026 21:00:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] drm/i915/psr: allow Panel Replay exit when psr.active is false

Panel Replay's psr.active software flag is not reliably
synchronized with hardware state. Allow intel_psr_exit() to
proceed when Panel Replay is enabled even if psr.active is false.

Signed-off-by: Gaggery Tsai <gaggery.tsai@intel.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_psr.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_psr.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_psr.c
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_psr.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_psr.c
@@ -2229,7 +2229,7 @@
 	enum transcoder cpu_transcoder = intel_dp->psr.transcoder;
 	u32 val;
 
-	if (!intel_dp->psr.active) {
+	if (!intel_dp->psr.active && !intel_dp->psr.panel_replay_enabled) {
 		if (transcoder_has_psr2(display, cpu_transcoder)) {
 			val = intel_de_read(display,
 					    EDP_PSR2_CTL(display, cpu_transcoder));
